{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-02",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_02_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 2 - Death in the Fog",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 5,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 975.7,
  "page_end_sec": 1216.24,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.753,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 975.7,
      "end": 976.78,
      "text": "It ain't right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 977.0,
      "end": 978.72,
      "text": "and it won't get you anywheres."
    },
    {
      "start": 979.5,
      "end": 980.928,
      "text": "We got our work to do.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 982.272,
      "end": 983.56,
      "text": "Lieutenant Dundee jumped up,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 983.6,
      "end": 984.94,
      "text": "stood close to Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 985.06,
      "end": 986.18,
      "text": "and thrust his square,"
    },
    {
      "start": 986.3,
      "end": 988.28,
      "text": "pink face up at the taller man's."
    },
    {
      "start": 989.568,
      "end": 990.54,
      "text": "\"'I've told you before,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 990.76,
      "end": 993.31,
      "text": "your foot was going to slip one of these days.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 994.816,
      "end": 996.32,
      "text": "Spade made a deprecative mouth,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 996.54,
      "end": 997.44,
      "text": "raising his eyebrows."
    },
    {
      "start": 999.008,
      "end": 1003.26,
      "text": "\"'Everybody's foot slips sometime,' he said with derisive mildness.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1003.74,
      "end": 1006.336,
      "text": "And maybe this is your time?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1007.392,
      "end": 1008.86,
      "text": "Spade smiled and shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1009.6,
      "end": 1010.06,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 1010.94,
      "end": 1011.54,
      "text": "I'll do nicely,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1011.7,
      "end": 1012.12,
      "text": "thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 1012.68,
      "end": 1014.2,
      "text": "He stopped smiling."
    },
    {
      "start": 1015.04,
      "end": 1018.14,
      "text": "His upper lip on the left side twitched over his eye-tooth.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1018.96,
      "end": 1020.8,
      "text": "His eyes became narrow and sultry.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1021.68,
      "end": 1023.83,
      "text": "His voice came out deep as the lieutenant's.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1024.736,
      "end": 1026.04,
      "text": "I don't like this.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1026.74,
      "end": 1027.96,
      "text": "What are you sucking around for?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.66,
      "end": 1030.78,
      "text": "Tell me or get out and let me go to bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 1031.872,
      "end": 1032.42,
      "text": "Who's Thursby?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1033.152,
      "end": 1033.58,
      "text": "Dundee snapped."
    },
    {
      "start": 1034.44,
      "end": 1036.32,
      "text": "\"'I told Tom what I knew about him.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1037.14,
      "end": 1038.56,
      "text": "\"'You told Tom damn little.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1039.34,
      "end": 1040.56,
      "text": "\"'I knew damned little.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1041.62,
      "end": 1042.7,
      "text": "\"'Why were you tailing him?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1043.552,
      "end": 1044.28,
      "text": "\"'I wasn't.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1044.3,
      "end": 1045.1,
      "text": "Miles was."
    },
    {
      "start": 1045.86,
      "end": 1046.72,
      "text": "For the swell reason",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1047.24,
      "end": 1048.92,
      "text": "that we had a client who was paying good"
    },
    {
      "start": 1048.92,
      "end": 1051.0,
      "text": "United States money to have him tailed.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1051.936,
      "end": 1052.47,
      "text": "\"'Who's the client?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1054.176,
      "end": 1056.7,
      "text": "Placidity came back to Spade's face and voice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1057.38,
      "end": 1058.2,
      "text": "\"'Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1058.2,
      "end": 1060.38,
      "text": "now,' he said reprovingly."
    },
    {
      "start": 1061.06,
      "end": 1062.84,
      "text": "You know I can't tell you that until"
    },
    {
      "start": 1062.84,
      "end": 1064.44,
      "text": "I've talked it over with the client."
    },
    {
      "start": 1065.52,
      "end": 1067.34,
      "text": "You'll tell it to me or you'll tell it in court,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1068.16,
      "end": 1069.02,
      "text": "Dundee said hotly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1069.78,
      "end": 1071.6,
      "text": "This is murder and don't forget it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1072.72,
      "end": 1073.04,
      "text": "Maybe.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1073.88,
      "end": 1075.66,
      "text": "And here's something for you to not forget,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1075.8,
      "end": 1076.08,
      "text": "sweetheart."
    },
    {
      "start": 1077.12,
      "end": 1078.98,
      "text": "I'll tell it or not as I damned please.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1080.288,
      "end": 1081.94,
      "text": "It's a long while since I burst out",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1081.94,
      "end": 1083.98,
      "text": "crying because policemen didn't like me."
    },
    {
      "start": 1085.5,
      "end": 1087.56,
      "text": "Tom came over and sat on the foot of the bed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1087.76,
      "end": 1089.82,
      "text": "His carelessly shaven,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1089.84,
      "end": 1092.04,
      "text": "mud-smeared face was tired and lined."
    },
    {
      "start": 1093.44,
      "end": 1094.02,
      "text": "\"'Be reasonable,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1094.18,
      "end": 1095.48,
      "text": "Sam,' he pleaded."
    },
    {
      "start": 1095.86,
      "end": 1096.92,
      "text": "\"'Give us a chance."
    },
    {
      "start": 1097.64,
      "end": 1099.46,
      "text": "How can we turn up anything on Miles's"
    },
    {
      "start": 1099.46,
      "end": 1101.79,
      "text": "killing if he won't give us what you've got?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1103.08,
      "end": 1106.04,
      "text": "\"'You needn't get a headache over that,' Spade told him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1106.848,
      "end": 1108.08,
      "text": "\"'I'll bury my dead.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1109.28,
      "end": 1112.1,
      "text": "Lieutenant Dundee sat down and put his hands on his knees again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1113.12,
      "end": 1114.88,
      "text": "His eyes were warm green discs.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1116.224,
      "end": 1117.18,
      "text": "\"'I thought you would,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1117.58,
      "end": 1117.92,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1118.08,
      "end": 1120.06,
      "text": "He smiled with grim content."
    },
    {
      "start": 1121.248,
      "end": 1123.5,
      "text": "That's just exactly why we came to see you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1123.56,
      "end": 1124.4,
      "text": "isn't it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1124.44,
      "end": 1124.64,
      "text": "Tom?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1125.94,
      "end": 1128.02,
      "text": "Tom groaned but said nothing articulate.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1129.184,
      "end": 1130.76,
      "text": "Spade watched Dundee warily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1132.48,
      "end": 1134.02,
      "text": "That's just what I said to Tom,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1134.66,
      "end": 1135.62,
      "text": "the lieutenant went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 1136.192,
      "end": 1136.72,
      "text": "I said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1136.74,
      "end": 1137.22,
      "text": "Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1137.49,
      "end": 1140.14,
      "text": "I've got a hunch that Sam Spade's a man"
    },
    {
      "start": 1140.14,
      "end": 1142.2,
      "text": "to keep the family troubles in the family."
    },
    {
      "start": 1143.072,
      "end": 1144.36,
      "text": "That's just what I said to him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1145.888,
      "end": 1147.8,
      "text": "Spade put the weariness out of his eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1148.13,
      "end": 1149.8,
      "text": "He made them look bored."
    },
    {
      "start": 1150.36,
      "end": 1151.92,
      "text": "He turned his face to Tom"
    },
    {
      "start": 1152.1,
      "end": 1153.62,
      "text": "and asked with great carelessness,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1154.912,
      "end": 1156.37,
      "text": "\"'What's itching your boyfriend now?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1157.6,
      "end": 1159.3,
      "text": "Dundee jumped up and tapped Spade's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1159.3,
      "end": 1161.24,
      "text": "chest with the ends of two bent fingers."
    },
    {
      "start": 1162.848,
      "end": 1164.38,
      "text": "\"'Just this,' he said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1164.42,
      "end": 1166.8,
      "text": "taking pains to make each word very distinct,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1167.2,
      "end": 1169.16,
      "text": "emphasizing them with repeated taps."
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.41,
      "end": 1173.36,
      "text": "Thursby was shut down in front of his hotel just",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1173.36,
      "end": 1176.02,
      "text": "thirty-five minutes after you left Burrett Street."
    },
    {
      "start": 1177.92,
      "end": 1178.5,
      "text": "Spade spoke,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1178.8,
      "end": 1180.74,
      "text": "taking equal pains with his words."
    },
    {
      "start": 1182.28,
      "end": 1185.18,
      "text": "Keep your damned dirty paws off me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1186.624,
      "end": 1188.22,
      "text": "Dundee withdrew the tapping fingers,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1188.44,
      "end": 1190.44,
      "text": "but there was no change in his voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 1192.16,
      "end": 1194.56,
      "text": "Tom says you were in too much of a hurry",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1194.56,
      "end": 1196.62,
      "text": "to even stop for a look at your partner."
    },
    {
      "start": 1198.08,
      "end": 1199.54,
      "text": "Tom growled apologetically.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1200.32,
      "end": 1200.84,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1200.84,
      "end": 1201.32,
      "text": "damn it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1201.34,
      "end": 1201.56,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1201.98,
      "end": 1203.22,
      "text": "you did run off like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 1204.34,
      "end": 1207.08,
      "text": "You didn't go to Archer's house to tell his wife.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1207.9,
      "end": 1209.76,
      "text": "The lieutenant's accusing voice went on.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1210.34,
      "end": 1212.02,
      "text": "We called up and that girl in your"
    },
    {
      "start": 1212.02,
      "end": 1214.16,
      "text": "office was there and said you sent her."
    },
    {
      "start": 1215.52,
      "end": 1216.24,
      "text": "Spade nodded.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}